cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on data protection and security through encryption and dispersion.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses parallel and distributed architectures for implementing the proposed system.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses fragmentation of information considering data defined along an object-oriented data structure or along a record structure to be stored in a relational database.
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper discusses fragmentation of information in the context of storing data in a relational database.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the design and implementation of a fragmentation, encryption, and dispersion system.
